    <title><![CDATA[You and Your Customer]]></title>
    <descriptionText><![CDATA[<font face="helvetica" size="3"><Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px; padding:0 0 0 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">You and Your Customer</Introtext><welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">You are a Hospital Account Manager with OAPI.  You’ve been with the company for two years and have an additional seven years of pharmaceutical sales experience with another company.  During your time with OAPI, you’ve maintained a successful track record of growing your accounts, and you have earned a reputation as a top performer.  Recently you met with Annie DeMarco, your District Manager, to review your target list and business plan.  Coming out of that meeting, you have identified Maycomb Community Hospital as one of the top accounts that you will focus on for the coming year, based on their prescribing potential.<BR><BR><span style="color:#3366cc; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Mackenzie “Mack” Miller (Your Mentor):</span><BR>A veteran sales manager and successful relationship builder, Mack is highly respected throughout the company and by customers. A testament to his fierce attention to his customers, a sign on Mack’s desk reads, “This conversation will be interrupted only when a customer calls.” Mack is always ready with a genuine smile and a kind word for everyone he meets. People are often surprised to learn that he is an accomplished skydiver, with more than 100 successful jumps.</welcomeText><br><lasttext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; color:#000; background-color:#c0c0c0; margin:10px; padding:2px 0 2px 5px; display:block;"><i>Please click the <b>CONTINUE</b> button to move to the next screen.</i></lasttext>]]></descriptionText>
